34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_MainGateRideDestos\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;City Stable Routes from the Main Gate\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingateridedestos.png?w=396\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingateridedestos.png?w=396\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingateridedestos.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"396\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingateridedestos.png 396w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingateridedestos.png?w=150\u0026amp;h=104 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 396px) 100vw, 396px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135831\"\u003eCity Stable Routes from the Main Gate\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI went and did my run up the place.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135828\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135828\" data-attachment-id=\"135828\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_uparamp/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"2860,1340\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_UpARamp\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;The ramps are spacious\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=1200 1200w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_uparamp.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135828\"\u003eThe ramps are spacious\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt is easy enough to ride a normal mount through the city, and you will likely want to.  Your mounted combat mount is also an option in the lower levels, but as you go further up the city the concourse between the lower and upper wall on each grows more and more narrow, until you get up to the fifth or sixth tier where there are parts where two grown men might have an issue walking side by side and the bends and twists make it likely you and your mount will get caught up in the scenery.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe city is amazingly well crafted and alive with NPCs.  You can be the only player in the city and it feels quite alive in a way that other MMO towns and cities often do not.  From the top ring looking down you can see the buildings of the rings in a cascade down to the main wall.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135832\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135832\" data-attachment-id=\"135832\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_lookingdowntherings/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"2860,1340\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_LookingDownTheRings\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Looking down on the lower tiers\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=1200 1200w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_lookingdowntherings.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135832\"\u003eLooking down on the lower tiers\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd a lot of the buildings… more than one might reasonably expect… are fleshed out inside, often well beyond the meager needs of whatever quest you might be running.  You can go from the throne room, where the chair of the Steward of Gondor sits on the bottom step, to dining areas, inns, crafting halls, stables, training rooms, and other locations.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135834\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135834\" data-attachment-id=\"135834\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_kingsthrone/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1200,562\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_Kingsthrone\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;The throne of the missing king and the steward’s chair\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg 1200w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_kingsthrone.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135834\"\u003eThe throne of the missing king and the steward’s chair\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThere is even a room with a model of the city in it, which is a bit meta I suppose.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135845\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135845\" data-attachment-id=\"135845\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_modelofminastirith/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"1269,662\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_ModelOfMinasTirith\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Model of Minas Tirith\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"313\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=1200 1200w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_modelofminastirith.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135845\"\u003eModel of Minas Tirith\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt’s only a model.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd, of course, the usual suspects show up.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135841\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135841\" data-attachment-id=\"135841\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_mithrandir/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"780,375\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_Mithrandir\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Working under a different name, eh G?\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg?w=768 768w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_mithrandir.jpg 780w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135841\"\u003eWorking under a different name, eh G?\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd, you know one of the hobbits has to be around somewhere.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135840\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135840\" data-attachment-id=\"135840\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_pippin/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"770,424\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_Pippin\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;See what offering up your sword got you\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"330\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg?w=768 768w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pippin.jpg 770w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135840\"\u003eSee what offering up your sword got you\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt is all way over the top honestly, and pushes the edge of the games ability to render.  I was in a couple of lavishly appointed, fully populated buildings and the video became pretty choppy.  It wasn’t stressing the video card, which barely deigns to spin up its fans when I play \u003cem\u003eLOTRO\u003c/em\u003e.  Rather, I think the client itself was barely up to the task.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAll of which is extremely impressive.  A pity there isn’t much interesting to do.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI mean, you get the whole Pippin treatment from Bergil, the son of Beregond of the guards of the citadel.  Bergil must just stand by the front gate looking for suckers or some such, as he clearly has a routine worked up of places to visit and treats to obtain using you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI suppose if you like the quests in the Shire where you run around to different inns or whatnot, then the Minas Tirith quests are not so bad.  You root our fifth columnists and deal with a troupe of actors and mediate a dispute between Beregond and his brother.  But a lot of it is a transparent effort to make you go digging around the city… and while the city is impressive, the tasks quickly become tedious.  I mean, did I really need to go collect the dirty towels from the bath house of the citadel?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135835\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135835\" data-attachment-id=\"135835\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_bathhousebetty/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"784,435\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_BathhouseBetty\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Seriously, this was a thing\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"333\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg?w=768 768w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_bathhousebetty.jpg 784w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135835\"\u003eSeriously, this was a thing\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd then there was the whole thing with the chicken, which is exactly the reason you need to keep the troops busy or they start coming up with stuff like… well.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135837\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135837\" data-attachment-id=\"135837\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_chickenexperiment/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"707,374\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_ChickenExperiment\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;There went the chicken\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"317\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_chickenexperiment.jpg 707w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135837\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eAs God as my witness, I thought chickens could fly\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt is actually kind of far down to the main gate from up there on the prow of the ship that juts out through the middle of the city, a reminder that the king and his people came from Numenor over the sea.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135833\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135833\" data-attachment-id=\"135833\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_maingatefromthetop/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"2288,1072\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_MainGateFromTheTop\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Still… it is a long way down\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=1200 1200w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_maingatefromthetop.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135833\"\u003eStill… it is a long way down\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI did as much of that as I could, balancing the tedium of so many “run across town and talk to a guy” quests with my sightseeing.  Eventually the tedium beat down my curiosity and I went back out the front gate and into the Pelennor.  That too is overwrought and over built.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-shortcode=\"caption\" id=\"attachment_135838\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg\"\u003e\u003cimg aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-135838\" data-attachment-id=\"135838\" data-permalink=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/2025/06/13/arrival-in-minas-tirith/mp26_pelennor/\" data-orig-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg\" data-orig-size=\"2860,1340\" data-comments-opened=\"1\" data-image-meta=\"{\u0026#34;aperture\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;credit\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;camera\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;caption\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;created_timestamp\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;copyright\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;focal_length\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;iso\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;shutter_speed\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;title\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;orientation\u0026#34;:\u0026#34;0\u0026#34;}\" data-image-title=\"MP26_Pelennor\" data-image-description=\"\" data-image-caption=\"\u0026lt;p\u0026gt;Out in the fortifications that have been overrun by the enemy\u0026lt;/p\u0026gt;\n\" data-medium-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=500\" data-large-file=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=600\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"281\" srcset=\"https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=600 600w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=1200 1200w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=150 150w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=500 500w, https://tagn.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/mp26_pelennor.jpg?w=768 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"caption-attachment-135838\"\u003eOut in the fortifications that have been overrun by the enemy\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut it has the advantage of being rife with orcs and easterlings and other servants of Sauron, with a series of quests dedicated to slaying them.  What else does a mysterious, heavily armed drifter with a history of violence really need?  Plus I need to get leveled up to trigger the battle of Pelennor so I can see that and then move on to Mordor.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIt is getting closer.  I can feel it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
